# Project standards

## General
- Comments: use `//` only; no `/** */`.
- Terminal: chain with `;`, never `&&`.
- Controller/model/view: one folder per entity, files inside.
- Development phase: update existing migration files; do not create follow-up migrations unless user explicitly asks.
- New tables: soft delete; add created_by, updated_by (Traits fill them).
- Reusable first: table, select, action buttons, createdbyinfo; default Save/Close/Cancel/Update with spinner while processing.
- Table actions: show spinner on click until success, then next action.

## API controllers
- Extend `App\Http\Controllers\BaseController` (not Controller).
- Use BaseController methods only; no raw `response()->json(...)`.
- Success: `$this->successResponse($data, $message, $code)` → `{ success: true, message, data }`
- Errors: `validationErrorResponse`, `unauthorizedResponse`, `forbiddenResponse`, `notFoundResponse`, `errorResponse`.

## Vue SFC
- Order: **script** → **template** → **style**.
- Use `<script setup>` only; clear names, short functions, minimal nesting.
- Prefer short expressions and helpers over long blocks.
- No need to build if need user will ask.
